Deputy President William Ruto on Thursday hosted the Commonwealth Secretary-General, Patricia Scotland at his Karen Office. Ruto recognized the Commonwealth’s approval of Kenya's peaceful campaigns. "We commit to working closely with the association towards free, fair, transparent and democratic elections that will pave the way to a smooth transition after the August polls," he added. The Cabinet Administrative Secretary(CAS) Ministry of Foreign Affairs Ababu Namwamba and other Commonwealth officials were present. Scotland is in Kenya to grace the 21st Conference of Commonwealth Education Ministers (CCEM) which started on Wednesday. The two-day conference focused on the theme, ‘Rethinking Education for Innovation, Growth and Sustainability post-Covid-19’. The conference has been hosted by the Government of Kenya in collaboration with the Commonwealth Secretariat and the Ministry of Education.